    "body": "I've been tripped up by this too, I've thought about writing a lint that detects when a function/method is being called directly inside itself on the same arguments but never got around to it; I don't think it would be too hard, but I'm not sure. (Happy to mentor if someone feels like doing this; find me here, on IRC as `huon` or via email (in my github profile).)\n\n> but presumably LLVM eliminates the recursive call to testcase::&'a T.Tag::to_tag somehow\n\nYes, LLVM optimises away side-effect-less infinite recursions sometimes: http://llvm.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=965\n",
